video.title: Anne with an E
video.synopsis: A plucky orphan whose passions run deep finds an unlikely home with a spinster and her soft-spoken bachelor brother. Based on "Anne of Green Gables."

episodes.synopsis: A bungled message brings spirited orphan Anne Shirley to Green Gables, where unmarried siblings Matthew and Marilla Cuthbert are waiting for a boy.
episodes.title: Your Will Shall Decide Your Destiny

episodes.synopsis: A determined Matthew embarks on a journey to bring Anne home. Marilla is sick with worry but struggles to express her emotions.
episodes.title: I Am No Bird, and No Net Ensnares Me

episodes.synopsis: Anne starts school in Avonlea and discovers she has much to learn. Marilla steps out of her comfort zone to attend a meeting for progressive mothers.
episodes.title: But What Is So Headstrong as Youth?

episodes.synopsis: A minister's advice prompts Marilla to question her choices. When tragedy strikes, Anne's intellect saves lives -- and her sullied reputation.
episodes.title: An Inward Treasure Born

episodes.synopsis: Anne hosts Diana for her first "grown-up" tea, but the affair proves a bit too intoxicating. Matthew runs an errand of utmost importance.
episodes.title: Tightly Knotted to a Similar String

episodes.synopsis: Anne's resourcefulness mends fences with the Barrys when Minnie May falls gravely ill. An affecting loss stirs up memories of Marilla's past.
episodes.title: Remorse Is the Poison of Life

episodes.synopsis: With the future of Green Gables at stake -- and an ailing Matthew confined to bed -- Anne and Marilla move mountains to save their home.
episodes.title: Wherever You Are Is My Home

episodes.synopsis: The Cuthberts' boarders stir excitement with a question: Could there be gold in Avonlea? Elsewhere, Gilbert makes a new friend at sea.
episodes.title: Youth Is the Season of Hope

episodes.synopsis: The steamer lands in Trinidad, bringing Bash face to face with his past. The Barrys get behind the gold rush, but Matthew and Marilla aren't so sure.
episodes.title: Signs Are Small Measurable Things, But Interpretations Are Illimitable

episodes.synopsis: An adventure away with the Barrys teaches Anne to trust her instincts. Marilla begins to suspect that her boarders aren’t as innocent as they seem.
episodes.title: The True Seeing Is Within

episodes.synopsis: Anne writes letters as an "agent of romance" while Diana trains at home to be a lady. A life-changing encounter steers Gilbert toward his destiny.
episodes.title: The Painful Eagerness of Unfed Hope

episodes.synopsis: A game of spin the bottle prompts burning questions about love and beauty. Anne and Cole bond over their differences as Gilbert makes his way home.
episodes.title: The Determining Acts of Her Life

episodes.synopsis: Anne faces the world with a shocking new look while the town preps for its annual Christmas pantomime. Gilbert and Bash join the Cuthberts for dinner.
episodes.title: I Protest Against Any Absolute Conclusion

episodes.synopsis: Cole accompanies the girls to Aunt Josephine's for a lavish party filled with surprises. Back at home, Marilla's health takes a worrisome turn.
episodes.title: Memory Has as Many Moods as the Temper

episodes.synopsis: With a wedding on the horizon, Anne wonders what kind of bride she'd like to be. Marilla sees an oculist, and Bash meets a friendly face in "The Bog."
episodes.title: Struggling Against the Perception of Facts

episodes.synopsis: A brand-new teacher brings unconventional methods -- and a motorbike -- to Avonlea. Gilbert's plan to speed up his studies leaves Bash feeling lost.
episodes.title: What We Have Been Makes Us What We Are

episodes.synopsis: Anne rallies her friends to save Miss Stacy in the wake of a disastrous incident. Bash gets an unexpected gift, and Cole makes a surprising choice.
episodes.title: The Growing Good of the World

episodes.synopsis: Anne meets a kindred spirit from a nearby Mi'kmaq village, then launches a bold quest for her 16th birthday: to learn about her lineage.
episodes.title: A Secret Which I Desired to Divine

episodes.synopsis: Anne revisits Saint Albans Orphanage to ask about her birth parents, and Mary's son Elijah returns home. Rachel decides Miss Stacy needs a suitor.
episodes.title: There Is Something at Work in My Soul Which I Do Not Understand

episodes.synopsis: As Easter approaches, Mary falls seriously ill, and everyone steps in to help. The government opens a residential school in Halifax.
episodes.title: What Can Stop the Determined Heart

episodes.synopsis: While Bash looks for Elijah in Charlottetown, Anne vows to finish her search -- with or without Marilla's blessing. Back home, Diana longs for adventure.
episodes.title: A Hope of Meeting You in Another World

episodes.synopsis: A dance practice stirs unfamiliar feelings between Anne and Gilbert. A desperate Bash writes to his mother in Trinidad.
episodes.title: I Am Fearless and Therefore Powerful

episodes.synopsis: At the county fair, Anne consults a fortune teller who claims to see love in her future. A nervous Gilbert prepares to meet Winifred's parents.
episodes.title: The Summit of My Desires

episodes.synopsis: After speaking her mind in print, Anne inflames the town -- but she refuses to be silenced. A secret drives Anne and Diana apart.
episodes.title: A Strong Effort of the Spirit of Good

episodes.synopsis: Ka'kwet runs away from school, and Miss Stacy weighs her options in the wake of tragedy. Aunt Josephine urges Diana to take the Queens entrance exam.
episodes.title: Great and Sudden Change

episodes.synopsis: Anne confesses her feelings for Gilbert -- but is she too late? Meanwhile, Matthew helps Ka'kwet's family, and Bash's mother adapts to life in Avonlea.
episodes.title: A Dense and Frightful Darkness

episodes.synopsis: Change is in the air as Anne turns toward college to start the next chapter of her life. It's her biggest adventure to date.
episodes.title: The Better Feelings of My Heart
